Package mrbaxmypka.gmail.com.mapPointsTrimmer.services

Class GoogleIconsService

java.lang.Object
mrbaxmypka.gmail.com.mapPointsTrimmer.services.GoogleIconsService
@Component
public class GoogleIconsService
extends java.lang.Object
Google Earth has special hrefs to icons as "http://maps.google.com/" which internally redirect to its local image store. Thus those types of hrefs aren't retrieved from the Internet within Google Earth BUT will require the Internet from any other application. So not to use Internet next time, if the given href starts with MAPS_GOOGLE_URL this class will try do download the icon or replace this href with the previously downloaded icon (if any).

  • Method Details

    • processIconHref

      public java.lang.String processIconHref​(java.lang.String href, MultipartDto multipartDto)
      Google Earth has special href to icons it internally redirects to it local image store. If the given href starts with MAPS_GOOGLE_URL this method will try do download the icon.
      Parameters:
      href - Href or src to an icon to be evaluated
      multipartDto - To examine its current icons and images cache MultipartDto#getImagesNamesFromZip() (if any) whether such an icon is already present among archive.
      Returns:
      If the given href don't start with MAPS_GOOGLE_URL the initial href will be returned. If the given user zip archive contains the icon name from the given href, the icon name without url will be returned. Otherwise this method will try to download the icon and return the downloaded icon filename of the initial url if failed.

    • getDownloadedHref

      private java.lang.String getDownloadedHref​(java.lang.String googleUrl, MultipartDto multipartDto)
      Parameters:
      googleUrl - An URL which starts with MAPS_GOOGLE_URL
      Returns:
      If a current zip archive from User contain an icon filename from the given URL that filename will be returned. Otherwise it will try to download the icon. If success, the filename of the downloaded icon will be returned, if isn't (e.g. no internet connection) it return the initial Google URL.

    • getIconFilename

      private java.lang.String getIconFilename​(java.lang.String googleHref)
      Parameters:
      googleHref - A full URL to an icon
      Returns:
      Only the icon filename without Internet address.

    • downloadIcon

      private java.lang.String downloadIcon​(java.lang.String googleUrl)
      If download success it will put an icon filename and bytes array into GoogleIconsCache.putIcon(String, byte[])
      Returns:
      A newly downloaded icon filename or the initial url if failed.
